      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Benchmark problems representative of contact mechanics and large-displacement beam bending must be solved to within published reference tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Each FEA platform was verified against NAFEMS benchmark LE1 and a cantilever beam contact reference problem. Residuals and energy errors are within 1% of reference solutions, satisfying the required level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study must demonstrate QoI change of less than 5% between successive refinement levels using at least three mesh densities.",
      "rationale": "Three mesh densities were evaluated (coarse ~85k, medium ~340k, fine ~1.2M elements). Stiffness and yield load QoIs changed by less than 3% between medium and fine meshes. Richardson extrapolation confirms discretization error below 2%."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver convergence criteria and nonlinear equilibrium residuals must be documented and shown to be below 0.1% force norm.",
      "rationale": "Newton-Raphson iteration used with force residual tolerance of 0.01%. Load step sensitivity study confirmed results are insensitive to step size within the range evaluated. Solver error is negligible relative to modeling uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation execution must be performed by qualified analysts following documented simulation plans; peer review of model setup must be recorded.",
      "rationale": "Simulation plans were reviewed and approved by senior analysts at each participating organization prior to execution. Model setup peer review records are archived. No use errors were identified during independent model audit."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The constitutive model and contact formulation must be justified relative to the physical mechanisms governing ASTM F1717 compression-bending response.",
      "rationale": "Elastic-perfectly plastic titanium alloy constitutive model is appropriate for the pre-yield regime of interest. Penalty-based frictional contact (mu=0.2) was validated against experimental slip measurements. Model form uncertainty is bounded by the ensemble spread across three independent FEA implementations."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties, geometry, and boundary conditions must be sourced from traceable measurements or certified material certificates; uncertainty ranges must be documented.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V material properties sourced from certified material test reports for the specific lot used in physical testing. Geometry derived from CMM measurements of test articles. Boundary conditions replicate F1717 fixture constraints. Parametric sensitivity study performed for ±10% variation in modulus and friction coefficient."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test sample population (N≥10) must be from production-representative lots with documented dimensional and material traceability.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs from a single production lot with full dimensional inspection and material certification. Sample-to-sample geometric variability was characterized and incorporated into the model input uncertainty assessment. Population is representative of commercial production."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios including at least two load magnitudes or configurations per ASTM F1717.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted at a single load configuration (5 mm offset, axial compression per F1717 standard setup). Only one test condition was evaluated, which is below the required level for this model risk level. This gap is acknowledged and documented as a known deficit; the assessment proceeds on the basis that the single condition is the most clinically relevant and conservative loading scenario."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation input parameters must be demonstrably equivalent to the physical test conditions within documented uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "Torque-controlled assembly of test constructs was replicated in the FEA via prescribed preload; equivalency confirmed by comparing predicted and measured axial stiffness in the linear regime. Input parameter mapping table reviewed by all three FEA teams and adjudicated for consistency."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metrics (mean error, prediction interval coverage) must be reported for all primary QoIs; statistical equivalence must be demonstrated.",
      "rationale": "Stiffness mean error: 7.3% (ensemble mean vs. experimental mean). Yield load mean error: 9.1%. Prediction intervals from the three-model ensemble bracket 10 of 11 experimental observations. U-pooled metric confirms adequate predictive accuracy for the intended submission use."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (construct stiffness and yield load) must be directly linked to the clinical performance endpoints and regulatory submission requirements.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield load under F1717 compression-bending are the primary regulatory QoIs for 510(k) submission of spinal implant systems. Linkage to clinical performance (fatigue life prediction, subsidence risk) is documented in the device risk analysis."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The validation activity must be conducted under conditions sufficiently similar to the intended use context that the results can be extrapolated with documented justification.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments replicate the ASTM F1717 protocol specified in the 510(k) predicate comparison. The non-cannulated 7.5 mm construct geometry, material, and loading conditions are identical to those in the intended submission. Extrapolation to clinical use is bounded by the device risk analysis and the scope stated in the claim and requirement nodes."
    }
